53897021.description: Used to add page metadata to HTML <head />.

53897034.about: Only fetch in batches of this size; for pagination

53897037.about: 0-based index of the paginated page to fetch

53897058.text: This includes edge cases and regression tests

53897077.text: 1 - Add pinned global variant to a new frame

53897089.text: Add a new frame named "newFrame" and pin (not target) the Dark global variant

53897128.text: Add a new frame named "newFrame" and pin (not target) the Dark global variant

53897134.text: 1 - Add pinned global variant to a new frame

53897146.text: 2 - Un-register and re-register a code component prop

53897152.text: Each branch un-registers and re-registers the prop "param1" of "CodeComp", and provides a value to it

53897191.text: 3 - Move existing node into TplSlot's default contents

53897251.text: 4 - Move existing node into TplComp with no slot arg

53897259.text: Move "section4tpl" into "section4comp" slot, which doesn't initially have a slot arg

53897310.text: 5 - Move existing node between two existing TplComp children

53897386.text: 6 - Delete tpl in one branch, move it inside a TplSlot in the other

53897392.text: Update "Section6Comp": one branch deletes "tpl" and the other moves it into the slot's default contents

53897445.text: 7 - Delete tpl in one branch, move it inside TplComp in the other

53897451.text: One branch deletes "section7tpl" and the other moves it into "section7comp" slot arg

53897496.text: 8 - Each branch updates expression with the same value

53897502.text: Each branch will unset the value for "booleanProp" in "Section8Comp2" inside "Section8Comp1", and set it to true again. It shouldn't be a conflict

53897561.text: One branch will update the registration of "choiceParam" in "CodeComp" to change the label of the option

53897586.text: Each branch adds a different value to hover text of "section10tpl": "value1" and "value2"

53897607.text: 11 - Create conflict deeper in the tree under a node that moved

53897613.text: Move "section11tpl" from "section11container1" to "section11container2" in one branch. Both branches create a conflict with its width.

53897657.text: One branch deletes the slot in "Section12Comp", while the other duplicates "section12container1", creating a new tpl with a slot arg to that slot

53897718.text: 13 - Re-order TplComp children, and insert new child in another slot

53897724.text: Re-order "section13tpl1" and "section13tpl2". Add a new tpl "newTpl" to the other slot.
